Taiwanese Stock: Asia Cement, Formosa Plastics, Taiwan Cement

-- B y   W e i y i   L i m
-- 
2011-05-30T06:00:45Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-30/chang-hwa-eva-airways-formosa-plastics-taiwan-stocks-preview.html
Shares of the following companies had
unusual moves in  Taiwan  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 1:30 p.m. close.  The Taiex Index rose 13.68, or 0.2 percent, to 8,823.68.  Cement makers:  Asia Cement Corp. (1102)  (1102 TT) gained 4.8
percent to NT$39.45, the highest level since August 2008, and
 Taiwan Cement Corp. (1101)  (1101 TT) jumped 5.9 percent to NT$41.60,
after the island said on May 27 it will levy a provisional anti-
dumping tax on some Chinese cement products.  Formosa Group shares:  Formosa Plastics Corp. (1301)  (1301 TT)
dropped 3.5 percent to NT$109, the steepest slump since March 2.
 Nan Ya Plastics Corp. (1303)  (1303 TT) slid 5.5 percent to NT$77.30,
the lowest close since Jan. 18.  Formosa was told to halt operations at a plant by Taiwan’s
Yunlin County government, the company said in a statement to the
island’s stock exchange on May 27. It may lose NT$26 million
($904,000) a day from the halt. Nan Ya was also asked to stop
its plant in Faifeng village and may lose NT$8.4 million a day,
according to separate statements.  HTC Corp. (2498)  (2498 TT), the world’s largest maker of handsets
using Google Inc. and Microsoft operating systems, lost 0.9
percent to NT$1,170. The stock pared an earlier slump of 5.9
percent after the company denied reports in the Economic Daily
News and Commercial Times that said Microsoft Corp. plans to
raise royalty fees for using its applications in the Android
operating systems in handsets.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Weiyi Lim in Singapore at 
 wlim26@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
